(WiFi Not Connecting) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Keywords: wifi not connecting no internet wireless network issue cannot connect) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Steps to fix WiFi issues:) Tj T*
(1. Turn WiFi off and on again on your device.) Tj T*
(2. Forget the network and reconnect: Settings > WiFi > Forget > Reconnect.) Tj T*
(3. Restart your computer.) Tj T*
(4. Restart the router or access point \(unplug 30 seconds\).) Tj T*
(5. Run Windows Network Troubleshooter: Settings > Network > Troubleshoot.) Tj T*
(6. Update network adapter driver via Device Manager.) Tj T*
(7. Reset network settings: open CMD as admin, run: netsh winsock reset) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Common Issues:) Tj T*
(- Wrong password: Verify WiFi password with IT.) Tj T*
(- IP conflict: Run ipconfig /release then ipconfig /renew in CMD.) Tj T*
(- Limited connectivity: Check DHCP server is running.) Tj T*
ET

